04318nam a22005895i 9780226815893DE-B159720220524034747.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220524t20222022ilu    fo  d z      eng d  a9780226815893  a(DE-B1597)618182  a(OCoLC)1289373319  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  ailucUS-IL 4aHD9787.A2bB45 2022 7aSOC0000002bisacsh04a338.4/7685312231 aBenzecry, Claudio E., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut14aThe Perfect Fit :bCreative Work in the Global Shoe Industry /cClaudio E. Benzecry. 1aChicago : bUniversity of Chicago Press, c[2022] 4c©2022  a1 online resource (272 p.) :b57 halftones  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe Perfect Fit shows us how globalization works through the many people and places involved in making women’s shoes. We know a lot about how clothing and shoes are made cheaply, but very little about the process when they are made beautifully. In The Perfect Fit, Claudio E. Benzecry looks at the craft that goes into designing shoes for women in the US market, revealing that this creative process takes place on a global scale. Based on unprecedented behind-the-scenes access, The Perfect Fit offers an ethnographic window into the day-to-day life of designers, fit models, and technicians as they put together samples and prototypes, showing how expert work is a complement to and a necessary condition for factory exploitation. Benzecry looks at the decisions and constraints behind how shoes are designed and developed, from initial inspiration to the mundane work of making sure a size seven stays constant. In doing so, he also fosters an original understanding of how globalization works from the ground up. Drawing on five years of research in New York, China, and Brazil, The Perfect Fit reveals how creative decisions are made, the kinds of expertise involved, and the almost impossible task of keeping the global supply chain humming.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aFashion and globalization. 0aShoe industry. 0aWomen's shoesxDesign. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  ashoe, shoes, communication studies, sociology, sociological, globalization, international, women, gender, clothing, craft, craftsmanship, design, designer, designing, creative, creativity, fit models, technicians, ethnography, ethnographic, prototypes, samples, behind the scenes, new york, china, united states of america, brazil, fashion, supply chain, commodity, commodification, feet, standardization, business, factory, labor, workers, work.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishz978311099455108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022z9783110994520oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076650940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226815893423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226815893/original  a978-3-11-076650-9  University of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099455-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2022 Englishb2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DSLb2022